<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id5293ebeb-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s756"><num value="756">§ 756.</num><heading> Power to appoint</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Whenever a majority of the district judges of any district court cannot agree upon the appointment of any officer of such court, the chief judge shall make such appointment.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id5293ebec-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/923">62 Stat. 923</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id5293ebed-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id5293ebee-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 375 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s260">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 260</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1161">36 Stat. 1161</ref>; <date date="1919-02-25">Feb. 25, 1919</date>, ch.29, § 6, <ref href="/us/stat/40/1157">40 Stat. 1157</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1929-03-01/ch419">Mar. 1, 1929, ch. 419</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/45/1422">45 Stat. 1422</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1944-05-11/ch192">May 11, 1944, ch. 192</ref>, §§ 1, 3, <ref href="/us/stat/58/218">58 Stat. 218</ref>, 219).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Only part of <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s375">section 375 of title 28</ref>, U.S.C., 1940 ed., appears in this section. The remainder is incorporated in sections 136, 294 and 371 of this title.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The term “chief judge” was substituted for “senior district judge”. (See reviser’s note under <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s136">section 136 of this title</ref>.)</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Minor changes in phraseology were made.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
